LAGOS  – Maxwell Olusegun Njarika is a young man with vision on a mission. He wants to build a food village were all manner of food will be bought and sold. He is the Founder and Chief Executive Officer of Chowakazy Restaurant, based in the Lekki area of Lagos State. He spoke with Daily Independent on what motivated him to start the business; what he wants to achieve and his plan to revolutionise the food industry in the county and build the first food village in the country. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! He said that he has always had the plan to start a restaurant business and grow it into a food village but he did not have the resource to actualize his dream. However, that changed when Chief Temitope Ajayi, the chairman of Silicon Valley Nigeria Economic Development Inc, empowered some youths with interest-free loans in the Lekki area of Lagos State after the EndSARS protests in which businesses and properties were destroyed. Balogun, NDE Train 185 Youths, Women In Lagos Ajayi Empowers Protest Victims With Interest-Free Loans Njakazi said he was among the people that received the interest-free loan and he used his to start Chawakazy. He stated that the restaurant sells spaghetti, grilled chicken, grilled turkey, grilled catfish, tiger nut milk, zobo, jollof rice and others. He disclosed that a chef comes in and cooks the food, which is targeted at the youthful population. He added that the restaurant opens in the evening when people have returned from work and school in the area. The young entrepreneur said that the experience has been good and he is learning new things in the Nigerian business environment. He stated that his dream is expand the business into a food village where people can come into and experience all the food that is served in the country. He thanked Chief Ajayi for providing with the capital 